1.title: Ice Patrol
1.plot: National Geographic joins troopers patrolling the rowdy Arctic Man Ski and Sno-Go Classic, where roughly 10,000 people convene for physically demanding winter sports.

2.title: Crime on the Kenai
2.plot: Unforgiving terrain mixed with big city crime makes challenging work for troopers in Soldotna--a city on the Kenai Peninsula.

4.title: The Wild West
4.plot: Meet the men and women fighting crime in the Seward Peninsula--where alcohol leads to more than 95 percent of all crime.

5.title: Frontier Force
5.plot: Go inside one of the world's most unique law enforcement agencies as the Alaska State Troopers fight crime, enforce fish and game regulations, and conduct search and rescue operations in America's last frontier.

6.title: Drug Bust
6.plot: Despite its small-town feel and remote location, the western outpost of Bethel is plagued with alcohol and drug problems.

1.title: Spring Break Madness
1.plot: Follow troopers as they police the 25th annual Arctic Man festival that hosts more than 12,000 partygoers.

2.title: Arctic Force
2.plot: The troopers race to save a woman on the brink of suicide, and catch and transport a sex offender by snowmobile back to the mainland.

3.title: Justice Below Zero
3.plot: From the Mat-Su Valley to the Talkeetna Mountains, troopers are on the look-out for a stolen handgun and then join a search and rescue for lost snowmobilers.

4.title: Manhunt
4.plot: It's an all out manhunt in -33Â° temperatures when troopers scour the streets of Fairbanks in search of a fugitive.

5.title: Shots Fired
5.plot: An annual 200-mile snowmobile race across the frozen tundra of western Alaska means troopers have their hands full.

6.title: Armed and Dangerous
6.plot: The troopers are stretched thin when they are called to an alcohol-related motorcycle accident and then must respond to a domestic violence call.

7.title: High-Speed Chase
7.plot: Troopers pursue a felon in a high-speed chase, track down suspects across the remote wilderness, and hunt for missing rafters on the Tonsina River.

8.title: Crime Under the Midnight Sun
8.plot: The troopers must keep the peace over the holiday weekend by cracking down on underage drinking, halting disorderly conduct and handling some unusual characters.

9.title: Highway Hijinks
9.plot: Follow Troopers as they battle crime and enforce wildlife laws from the breathtaking Seward Highway to the Alaskan back country.

10.title: Operation Moose Decoy
10.plot: Troopers initiate "Operation Moose Decoy" to catch unsuspecting poachers.

11.title: Anchorage Undercover
11.plot: Troopers team up with the FBI to confront Anchorage's drug problem.

12.title: Vice Squad
12.plot: Troopers engage in a dangerous 90 mph pursuit until they apprehend the "dazed and confused" driver at gunpoint and find illegal drugs in the car.

13.title: Dazed and Confused
13.plot: Troopers and Anchorage PD chase down thieves and smugglers, set up prostitution stings with the VICE squad, catch drunk drivers, and regulate moose and caribou hunts.

1.title: Beers & Bears
1.plot: The streets of Fairbanks have turned into a race-track when a getaway car is on the loose with a freshly stolen firearm.

2.title: Grizzly Showdown
2.plot: This episode starts with a bang as the troopers respond to a call about gunshots and screams.

3.title: DUI on the 4th of July
3.plot: Get a glimpse into the hard work of being a trooper: from controlling out-of-control partiers on the Kenai Peninsula to a search-and-rescue on the melting ice in a remote village.

4.title: Spring Break Crazy
4.plot: Springtime in Alaska means one thing for thousands of adrenalinejunkies: Arctic Man. It's one of Alaska's most extreme sporting events and the biggest weeklong party of the year.

5.title: Cowboy Fugitive
5.plot: Deep in the rugged Talkeetna Mountains, Trooper John Cyr and rookie Trooper Scott Lanier are on the lookout for illegal hunters of sheep, caribou and moose.

6.title: Madman Manhunt
6.plot: In this hour-long adventure with "Alaska State Troopers," go behind the scenes as troopers patrol the streets and the wilderness of the final frontier.

7.title: Moose/Man Hunt
7.plot: From Alaska's toughest cities to its farthest reaches, troopers are on the hunt for armed and dangerous criminals as well as an abandoned moose, shot illegally by an eager hunter.

8.title: Gun N Hide
8.plot: When troopers respond to a call regarding a discharged gun in the Mat-Su Valley, they discover a large stash of weapons hidden inside a boat.

9.title: Midnight Poachers
9.plot: This hour-long journey with the "Alaska State Troopers" gives you a front row seat into the work of the first response in the last frontier, where suspects and beasts alike could be lurking around every corner.

10.title: Storm of the Century
10.plot: Troopers face a new set of challenges with an unforgiving blizzard setting in.

11.title: Warrant Wonderland
11.plot: In this riveting episode of Alaska State Troopers, the men and women in blue risk life and limb to protect the residents--and resident animals--of Alaska.

12.title: Helter Skelter Homicide
12.plot: Troopers set up decoys to catch unsuspecting illegal hunters, try to solve the mystery of a disappearing dead moose, uncover clues that lead them to a well-organized crime ring, and help investigate a bloody potential homicide scene.

13.title: Alaskan Standoff
13.plot: This one-hour episode of "Alaska State Troopers" takes you from Alaska's crime-ridden city of Fairbanks, all the way to Grayling, a remote village only accessible by plane.

14.title: Village Vigilantes
14.plot: Troopers go the distance in this episode of Alaska State Troopers, taking to land, air, and snow machine to bring justice to some of Alaska's most remote locations.

1.title: Extreme Justice
1.plot: Get the adrenaline flowing with this special episode that includes arrests in remote villages; helicopter rescues on frigid, 22 degree mountaintops; and dangerous suspect chase-downs in south central Alaska.

2.title: Knife Fight
2.plot: Snowflakes fall as Trooper Howie Peterson responds to a search and rescue call in the Kenai Peninsula: a snow-machiner accident where the victim may be dead or alive.

3.title: Alaska Chainsaw Massacre
3.plot: Winter has seized Alaska, and Trooper Timothy Cronin gets a chilling call.

4.title: Shotgun Showdown
4.plot: This episode starts with a bang as the troopers respond to a call about gunshots and screams. The hunt for the gunman leads them into the Fairbanks woods, where they find the suspect threatening to blow someone's head off. Then, on the waterways of western Alaska, the team must rein in some potentially volatile fishermen by both boat and float plane. Then, Trooper Stariha is hot on the trail of a fleeing motorcycle who suddenly takes the chase onto the crowded highway.

5.title: Armed and Bootlegging
5.plot: It's a criminal homebrew operation and Trooper Tim Smith is tackling it head-on. He's new to the remote post 30 miles north of the Arctic Circle and he must head into one of the most dangerous villages in the area - a "dry" village where illegal manufacturing of alcohol has gotten out of control and law enforcement has been run out of town.

6.title: Bloody Warrior
6.plot: It sounds like a tale out of a horror movie when troopers Aaron Mobley and Bill Connors set out to find a man who assaulted someone with a machete, leaving the victim bloodied and with a broken jaw. But after they make the arrest, the drama is far from over.

7.title: Campground Crazies
7.plot: In Alaska's Mat-Su Valley, Trooper Joseph Hess is called in to investigate an alarming discovery: campers have found remains that appear to be human toes and hands.

8.title: Grizzly-pendence Day
8.plot: Trooper Gabe Rich is called to a residence where renters are armed and have fired shots on anyone trying to enter their house.

9.title: Hostage Standoff
9.plot: When Alaska State Trooper Jared Noll goes to a call in Wasilla, where a man has a bear-hunting, high caliber rifle, will he get there in time before the gunman's girlfriend is harmed?

10.title: Armed & Squatting
10.plot: Alaska State Troopers must confront a man who is illegally living on public land, find a missing toddler who has disappeared into the woods, and track a man with a warrant as he tries to hide in a remote village on the Yukon River.

11.title: Meth Dealer Manhunt
11.plot: Watch as Trooper Hess tries to track a notorious drug dealer in the Matsu Valley. The man has ditched his car and his girlfriend, but will he slip away from Troopers?

12.title: Son and a Gun
12.plot: From a woman trapped in auto accident wreckage, to a romance gone sour, to crystal meth drug runners, Alaska's finest are put to the test of every challenge.

13.title: Drunk and Danger
13.plot: Danger is on the rise as flooding takes over south-central Alaska. A 17-inch storm surge and high winds have left thousands in danger and even uprooted residential homes.

14.title: Fatal Inferno
14.plot: A blazing inferno sends trooper David Lorring racing to save a disabled man's life in Soldotna.

15.title: Crystal Meth Compound
15.plot: Like a scene from an action movie, Troopers silently and swiftly surround the home of a well-known criminal suspected of hiding stolen guns.

16.title: Trooper Stalker
16.plot: Talk about a long commute! Trooper Massey must drive to the airport, catch an airplane and be picked up by a patrol boat to get from St.Mary's to Alakanuk.

17.title: Deep Woods Standoff
17.plot: Not only when standing in the line of fire during traffic pullovers, but also during undercover decoy operations, troopers must remain vigilant in all corners of the state so they aren't caught on their heels and in a deadly predicament.

18.title: Blacked Out & Belligerent
18.plot: Troopers are on the brink of chaos in one of the country's most remote states: from family feuds in the backwoods to bloody burglars to moose creating hazards on roadways, buckle up tight as you follow troopers into wild Alaska--to save lives and serve justice.

19.title: Hot Drugs, Icy Streets
19.plot: Alaska State Troopers not only deal with crime, but battle the elements in the vast, wild state--fom icy roads and high speed chases, to tourists lurking too close to brown bears, to freezing, wind chilled nights where burglars may be on the prowl, Alaska State Troopers take it all in stride.

20.title: Too Much Pot
20.plot: Winter has set in and Alaska and wildlife Trooper Jon Simeon patrols Alaska's newly frozen lakes when he hears a gunshot: someone has illegally killed two caribou.

21.title: Chopper Down
21.plot: From helicopter crash rescues and snow-machine decoys to missing people in subzero temperatures, Alaska State Troopers must face the danger that the last frontier has to throw at them.

1.title: Trail of Blood
1.plot: The Troopers face rising criminal behavior as spring beckons and the Iditarod heats up.

2.title: Loaded for Bear
2.plot: The Troopers must employ their best means of defense when culprits come out onto the Alaskan streets armed with knives, guns, and even rocks

3.title: Bear Aware
3.plot: The chase is on as Troopers pursue wanted criminals through cities and wilderness.

4.title: Lock'N'Load Neighbors
4.plot: The roads are teeming with trouble and the Troopers must dodge wintry conditions to catch their criminals.

5.title: Smell of Death
5.plot: Troopers must expect the unexpected when routine patrols turn into high-speed chases and citizens need help in the wilderness.

6.title: Burglars & Bears
6.plot: The streets of Fairbanks have turned into a race-track when a getaway car is on the loose with a freshly stolen firearm.

7.title: Hammered on the Holiday
7.plot: Trooper Dahl scans the wilderness for missing hunters in his floatplane, hoping he's not too late.

8.title: Carnival Chaos
8.plot: While the locals and tourists are out catching fish, the Troopers are out catching criminals on the dangerously swift currents of Alaska's waterways.

9.title: Wildest Calls
9.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

10.title: Battling Demons
10.plot: Troopers face unforeseen knife fights in isolated villages, respond to heinous car crashes, and battle drunk drivers on Alaska's most dangerous highway.

11.title: Frozen Justice
11.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

12.title: Shotgun Standoff
12.plot: Responding by land, air, and sea Troopers risk their lives to protect Alaskan citizens and wildlife.

1.title: Guns, Cash, & Coke
1.plot: The Troopers chase a wanted and dangerous man through a forest, clear small villages from illegal bootleggers, help a man under the influence of drugs, and protect the community from a curious bear.

2.title: Meth, Knives, & Spears
2.plot: The Troopers bring down a drug trafficking felon and stop illegal hunters from slaying helpless fowl, while Wildlife Troopers investigate the mysterious appearance of several trucks that have torn up a nature preserve in the Mat-Su Valley.

3.title: Burning Alaska
3.plot: The Troopers battle a crippling forest fire, handle a nail-biting standoff and take on a drug-filled traffic stop. With wilderness conditions out of their hands and a desperate gunman firing at random, Troopers never know how each shift will end.

4.title: One in the Chamber
4.plot: Illegal moose hunters are on the prowl in the mountains of the Mat-Su Valley and the Troopers set out to hunt them down. The Troopers track down and arrest international felons and detain a drugged up fisherman.

5.title: Crawl Space Capture
5.plot: On a dangerously cold winter night, the Troopers hunt for a man who is threatening to end his own mother's life. The Troopers let loose at the 53rd annual shooting competition against the Royal Canadian Mounted Police.

6.title: In the Line of Duty
6.plot: Follow the Alaska State Troopers as they help save lives in danger, from a father nearly stabbing his own son to death, to a man attempting to brave the negative winter temperatures in a tent, to the wee lives of crabs trapped in illegal pots.

7.title: Too Drunk to Drive
7.plot: From a hot pursuit on ice-covered roads to a moose disrupting busy streets, no patrol measures up to the bone-chilling magnitude as those of Alaska's state troopers. In Fairbanks, Trooper Rallo is in dangerous pursuit of a stolen vehicle. Down in Palmer, a call comes out to Trooper Taylor of a car accident involving a moose on the Glenn Highway, where thousands of drivers commute every day. In Homer, Trooper Chaffin searches for the suspect of a local burglary before he flees the state.

8.title: Cut in the Gut
8.plot: Troopers Noll, Taylor and Hess arrive on the scene of a crime of sheer brutality. A scorned ex-husband has been viciously stabbed, leaving him nearly eviscerated and on the verge of losing his life. In the Mat-Su Valley, Trooper Determan is called to investigate a rolled-over vehicle. When he and the paramedics arrive, they find the car in a frozen swamp with an unconscious man trapped inside. Then in Juneau, Wildlife Trooper Bjork investigates nearly 100 unattended shrimp pots in the waters.

9.title: Backwoods Bust
9.plot: Trooper Cronin is patrolling Palmer's slippery streets when he gets a call about a suspected drunk driver going in the wrong direction. Across the valley, Trooper Taylor investigates the theft of a $15,000 ATV and goes on a 12-hour hunt that leads him into the Alaska woods in the dead of night. North in Fairbanks, Trooper Mike Munson responds to a call that a man who threatened his former landlord's life is stalking outside the landlord's home.

10.title: Head-On Collision
10.plot: On the Parks Highway - the busiest stretch of road between Anchorage and Fairbanks - a head-on collision between an SUV and semi-truck shuts down the highway. Trooper Anderson arrives at the scene to find those in the SUV badly injured, and must work quickly with the emergency crew to save those whose lives are on the line. Across the valley, Trooper Noll responds to a burglary in progress and drives head-on into imminent danger, chasing after the suspect on ice-covered roads.

11.title: Cuff 'Em Countdown
11.plot:
Know what this is about?

1.title: Home Invasion Manhunt
1.plot: Follow the Troopers as they help to end a sibling dispute, catch illegal fur trappers in the Denali wilderness, and plunge into the icy waters of Goose Lake. Troopers are led on a manhunt to find the source of a menacing car horn, and also find the mother lode of marijuana stashes.

2.title: Hairy Threat
2.plot: The Troopers take down a joy riding felon on the icy streets of Fairbanks, save innocent pooches from the wrath of Alaskan wildlife, and patrol the dangerously thin icy waters of the Mat-Su Valley's most popular ice fishing lakes. Up north, Troopers are on the hunt for an out of control wild lynx who is wreaking havoc on the community's pets, and he might turn on the neighborhood kids next.

3.title: Extreme Drug Busts
3.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

4.title: 2-For-1 Takedown
4.plot: Follow the Troopers as they storm in to save a woman scorched by the out of control flames of a bonfire, track down a wanted and armed man through the frozen backcountry roads of Fairbanks, and start off the Iditarod race off with safety. Troopers also get a call from a well-known dogsledding family whose famous sleds have been burgled from their own home.

5.title: Fearless on the Front Lines
5.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

6.title: Contraband and Kitchen Knives
6.plot: Alaska State Troopers need to be willing to roll with the punches -- there's no such thing as an ordinary day on patrol. Join Troopers as they rescue a fallen hiker, keep the streets safe from life-threatening drunk drivers and track down a wanted man. Then, follow the latest class of recruits at the Alaska Public Safety Training Academy as they work to master the precision maneuver driving course.

7.title: Alaska's Most Wanted
7.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

8.title: NYPD to AST
8.plot: Alaska is the largest state in the U.S., which means Troopers have their work cut out for them when it comes to hunting down criminals on the loose. In the Mat-Su Valley, Troopers and K9s are tracking down thieves through the snowy backwoods. Meanwhile, a blaring horn could be a desperate call for help, so the Troopers split up to cover more ground. In Fairbanks, Troopers are on the hunt for an armed and aggressive home intruder

9.title: Rock Throwing Rampage
9.plot: Troopers scramble to rescue lost snowmobilers, help a stranded citizen, and recover a frozen body, lost to the harshness of the terrain.

10.title: Dead-End Deranged
10.plot: Follow the Troopers as they're swept into a high-speed chase with a dangerous felon, think on their toes when routine traffic stops are not what they seem, and deal with the worsening road conditions wreaking havoc on motorists.

11.title: Cliff Top Chaos
11.plot: State and Wildlife Troopers alike battle treacherous obstacles to keep the streets and forests of Alaska safe, from DUI's with surprise endings, to damsels in distress on rocky cliffs. Troopers also deal with erratic drivers and disturbance calls, proving the point in Alaska there is no such thing as a routine stop.

12.title: Drugged, Drunk, & Deranged
12.plot: Troopers go to the far reaches of the state to investigate a village store break-in. In Fairbanks, Troopers are called to respond to a repeat exposing violator at the local transfer station, and are faced with an aggressive confrontation.

13.title: Asleep at the Wheel
13.plot: Follow the heroes one last time as they refuse to give up in the face of danger, chase down burglary nightmares, and save lives that are on the brink of death. Troopers brave the severe conditions and the volatile criminals that ravage the state, without blinking an eye.

imdb.title: Alaska State Troopers
plot: Cameras ride along with Troopers as they keep the streets safe and hunters honest while at the same time taking advantage of the breathtaking landscape that _Alaska State Troopers_ (qv) are lucky enough to call "their office."::PSG Films
